Dealing with floppy disks!!! 

How to format a floppy disk in non standard capacity in ubuntu.

To format a 3.5 inch floppy disk in msdos 720k format in a usb floppy drive connected to your ubuntu system type:
> sudo ufiformat -f 720 -v /dev/sdd
> sudo mkdosfs -I /dev/sdd

Then you can mount the floppy and see if it works by:

> sudo mount /dev/sdd /mnt

Dont forget to unmount with:
> sudo umount /mnt

How to write an image file to your usb connected floppy in ubuntu:

> sudo dd if=diskimage.img of=/dev/sdd
